HEADWORD: Chutnee
<hw>Chut"nee</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind. <ets>chatn⟦imac⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A warm or spicy condiment or pickle made in India,
compounded of various vegetable substances, such as chopped fruits or
green tomatoes, etc., often cooked with sweets and acids such as sugar
and vinegar, with ginger and spices.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Indian relish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

